# Readability Spacing

Prefer a single blank line between variable declarations/assignments and the next control-flow statement to improve scanability.

Use this spacing for statements like `if`, `for`, `while`, and `repeat`.

Keep related declarations contiguous, then separate them from control flow with exactly one blank line.

Allow exceptions when a compact one-liner is clearly more readable.

```luau
-- Bad
local speed = characterSpeed
if speed > 20 then
	print("Fast")
end

-- Good
local speed = characterSpeed

if speed > 20 then
	print("Fast")
end
```
